The paper proposes a coding scheme for rewriting write-once memories, which involves encoding information using the positions of zero symbols. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with storage media and memory systems, which could place it in the Data Structures (cs.DS) or Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also mentions achieving high code rates, which could indicate a focus on Signal Processing (cs.SI) or Architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories.
